_exec_summary.SummaryText:
Grace Davison, Edison site has a Risk management Program which meets the requirement of OSHA-PSM, EPA-RMP and Program 3 NJ-TCPA Risk management Program. The site is an OSHA VPP Star Site and is certified for ISO 9001 Quality Management System.

a) Accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source.

The Edison site as of June 2006 has two occupants, Equistar Chemicals, LP, and Grace Davison. Equistar is the site owner and operates one large process; Grace owns three of the site buildings and operates other processes. Equistar provides and manages a broad spectrum of services to Grace including Utilities, Maintenance, shipping/receiving/warehousing and Emergency Response (ER) for both companies. To the extent possible, all Emergency Response programs apply to all site operations and both Equistar and Grace are co-owners of these programs.

The accidental release prevention policy at the Edison site is documented in the "Management System" document. It includes all the required elements of RMP including maintaining Process Safety Information, Employee Participation, Process Hazard Analysis and Risk Assessment, Standard Operating Procedures, Operator Training, Pre-startup Review, Mechanical Integrity, Hot Work Permit, Management of Change, Accident Investigation, Emergency Response, Compliance Audits, Contractors and Inherently Safe Technology review.

The Edison site strives to maintain a safe working environment, it is therefore essential that employees be able to deal effectively with emergencies that may develop during course of operations. Therefore, a multi-functional ER team (ERT) has been formed. The site ERT shall provide the actions necessary to control an emergency with the following priorities:
1.    To safeguard the lives of company personnel;
2.    To protect the well being of our visitors, contractors, truck drivers, neighbors and the community;
3.    To protect the environment;
4.    To protect company property.

